column5: No, we simply out logic you to death.

I was there at 7 and no one showed. I'll try 7 tonight.  We have a Christmas party every year and last year a couple who were coming for the 1st time ever showed up at 7:00 Friday evening and all dressed up. We opened the door and he said "we must be early cause there's no other cars in the driveway"  My wife said "yes you are, by 24 hours, the parties tomorrow night"  We still laugh about it every time we see them

If I don't make it look for my name in the Spec's obits Monday. It is with great sadness that we inform the board of Old Ironmaker's presumed passing. While not yet confirmed, it is believed that he has now passed from this mortal coil into the ether of eternity. We will miss you as we now have no-one left to tease about not making dates.
It may have been a small gathering, but it was a good GTG all the same despite the " possible passing" of one of our members.  Hey Dave!  The wife likes you.
wish i coulda made it! this Christmas rush at work has me working late nights!
Hey Dave! The wife likes you.  Dave has that effect on people.  Was good seeing you and the cast of usual's Bruce. Cheers.

It may have been a small gathering, but it was a good GTG all the same despite the " possible passing" of one of our members.  Hey Dave! The wife likes you. Thanks Bruce, it was nice talking to your wife.Say Merry Christmas to her, missed her leaving when I went to the washroom. Shame we couldn't get more people to come out, I guess close to Christmas and we all live miles apart. Plus the drinking and driving has put a stop to allot of functions. Thanks Kelvin for dropping Chris and myself off at my place, we had quite a filtered try again please chat at my place. Rest in peace Johnny, must have got snowed in or the sound of the waves put you to sleep. , What happened bud? Even Albert left early Still nice to see everyone.

Thanks Bruce, it was nice talking to your wife.Say Merry Christmas to her, missed her leaving when I went to the washroom. Shame we couldn't get more people to come out, I guess close to Christmas and we all live miles apart. Plus the drinking and driving has put a stop to allot of functions. No problem at all Dave,, Always fun to be with friends and I guess we had an early reception for Johnny the extra beer & wings were Good
Hey it is only 5 1/2 hours....
I owe a friend in Youngstown a visit I can swing by on the way home.
DEAL!  I'll pack some snacks!
Hope to see you there. I remember you saying we worked in the same dept. during a cutback. Man we are getting older, I left 15 years ago, let's see if I might recognize you Spiel.
If I wasn't trying to prep the house for sale and didn't have plans to do my Christmas drinking/shopping/drinking, I maybe woulda coulda.  Hopefully next year you guys will plan another...........?

Hope to see you there. I remember you saying we worked in the same dept. during a cutback. Man we are getting older, I left 15 years ago, let's see if I might recognize you Spiel.  Yes same department, I worked with F. Beattie and G. Love for the short time I was there under the direction of J. McKeag (sp). Oddly enough I ended up training McKeag's daughter a few years later on the plate mill cranes.  But that aside I'd bet I recognize you before you would me.

Yes I remember now, schedule clerks office next to ours. Uncle Frank, yes McKeag and Gerry Wright, Len Love was a Keeper on D and H&S rep. McKeags son is the asst. service manager at the dealership in Caledonia I take my truck to. Will catch up for sure.
What is there no more coming out.. everybody complains that we don't GTG and when we do only a few show up
Seriously, wish I could!

Seriously, wish I could! If you were closer you would be more than welcome.... this is why we have these GTG so we can all meet just like we use to at the Fire Hall.. Ah yes the Fire Hall,,, Chicken Wings and Beer  ... Good Old Days as many will remember

I think after the baby is born and we are in a bigger house and there isn't a million things for me to do, I'll have no excuse not to. I could bring my brothers and make it a weekend. I mentioned it last night to one of my bros and he said he would love to. Next year!
Wish I could guys. Dec 20th is Barbara's birthday and a night out with the boys probably would not be a positive move...
Heck, im in Buffalo..........shoulda had it down here, Ive got many award winning Buffalo Wing locations to choose from  lol
Wish I could guys. Dec 20th is Barbara's birthday and a night out with the boys probably would not be a positive move... John that is not a problem I will buy Barb a pound of Wings for her BIRTHDAY

It's on the calendar. Works out great as we have a party that night and it's on 56 in Binbrook so I can stop in the Creek for an hour or so then meet my lady at the Xmas party, perfect. If anyone from Hamilton wants at least a one way designated driver PM me, if I have 2 beers it's one over what I usually drink on a wild night on the town. I can't stay too long but unless you plan on closing the place I can drive you home after a few hours.  Look forward to it, again. Forgot last year to mark it down. Same goes for last months Stelco club meeting, again.

Same goes for last months Stelco club meeting, again.  You missed a good one JD. Aaron Shirley was our guest speaker (he did a great job!) for likely the largest crowd we've had to date.  Hope to see you at the G2G.

I know, I know. I really wanted to listen to Mr. Shirley. He sure knows his stuff. I now have to make notes for everything, then a note to remind me where I left the notes. Saturday I went grocery shopping and used the list from who knows when. Now if I find my note I need to date them. Hit my noggin one too many times on a Stock shed bin door.
